# LocatorJS Extension - Cursor IDE Configuration

## Project Overview
This is a Chrome/Firefox browser extension for LocatorJS that allows developers to click on UI components in the browser to open their code in their IDE.

## Tech Stack
- TypeScript
- SolidJS (for extension UI)
- Webpack (for bundling)
- Chrome Extension Manifest V3
- Monorepo structure with pnpm workspaces

## Code Style
- Use TypeScript strict mode
- Follow existing code patterns in the codebase
- Use SolidJS for UI components (not React)
- Extension uses Manifest V3 for Chrome

## Key Directories
- `apps/extension/` - Main extension code
- `packages/runtime/` - Runtime library
- `packages/shared/` - Shared utilities
- `packages/babel-jsx/` - Babel plugin for JSX source mapping

## Build Commands
- `pnpm build` - Build all packages
- `cd apps/extension && pnpm build` - Build extension only
- `cd apps/extension && pnpm dev` - Development mode with hot reload

## Extension Structure
- `src/manifest.v3.json` - Chrome extension manifest
- `src/pages/` - Extension pages (popup, options, etc.)
- `src/browser.ts` - Browser API abstraction
- Build output: `build/production_chrome/`

## Notes
- Extension requires development mode in target applications to work properly
- Uses babel-plugin-transform-react-jsx-source for source mapping
- Supports both Chrome (Manifest V3) and Firefox (Manifest V2)

